<br />
<br />
It runs.  Much like Dom&#39;s deck it uses the same principles of running, archery and skirmish cancelling to speed through to site 9.  the shadow is not for overwealming(aka no plae blade), but is good enough to slow them down alot.<br />
Afetr talking to dom over dmail i saw that his deck is a beast, but i didn&#39;t like how since you had to bid so high early, and add a burden early, you&#39;d be vulnerable to an early todea or enqua.  with this deck since you pull sam and start pippen, you can bid 7 no problem.<br />
Another thing with running decks is they give alot of pool early and are weak vs early overwealms...solution: Boromir.  combined with armor and fixed aragorn you have the best loop in teh game.  starting him is justhuge and the extra copies of aragorn and legos help you heal them for archery anyway.<br />
<br />
Aside from that its the same running 1-6 with stealths, 6-9 with archery shiot that alot of peeps been playing.  one note, sacrifice one of your . hobbits early so you dont have too many companions.  <br />
<br />
thats about it, i&#39;m a begineer but i dont see this game as being that hard, i think this deck is good...now to get the cards to play it.  peace fellas--h2o </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
